value.SummaryText:
Changes to our services due to COVID-19

This is a message to update all of our customers who use our pharmacy. 

These are extraordinary times and we are doing everything that we can to provide the best service under the circumstances whilst also keeping you and our staff safe.

These are challenging times for everyone and we appreciate many of you will be rightly concerned about what is to come in the weeks and months ahead. 

We are taking this very seriously and we are working very hard to maintain a normal service. 

Key changes we will be making:

OPENING HOURS 

We will be open to the public between as shown below hoever if necessary we may reduce our opening hours to 09:00 and 19:00. If there any further changes we will put posters up and update our website to reflect this. 

DELIVERY SERVICE 

We will offer free delivery to anyone who is 70 or over or who falls into an 'at increased risk' category* as defined by UK government for the duration of the pandemic.  We strongly encourage all those over 70 or in an 'at risk' group to stay at home and let us deliver to you. Please let staff know if you would like your medicines delivered in the local area. 

ORDERING PRESCRIPTIONS 

We are currently asking customers to order as usual 7 days in advance. But please allow 5 days for orders to be completed. 

A huge thankyou to all our customers for your understanding during this difficult times. We really do appreciate it!

PLEASE STAY SAFE AND LOOK AFTER YOURSELF

If you have any questions please email us on bournemouth.pharmacy@gmail.com as we may not be able to answer the telephone.

Meds at Home was the first Internet/Mail Order Pharmacy approved by NHS Dudley. 

This is a fairly new concept of pharmacy locally, and provides innovative methods to obtain NHS and private prescriptions. Although a different concept, we do provide services that you would expect from a typical 'High Street' pharmacy - please contact us for further information.

Meds at Home offers a professional, efficient, safe and convenient medicines supply service provided by a dedicated pharmacy team, delivering or posting your medicines to a location of your choice. You have the reassurance of dealing with a friendly pharmacy where we value each and every customer.

Our aim is to offer expertise, efficiency and reliability online to you in the comfort of your home or workplace.

Hobbs Pharmacy is owned and operated by Butt & Hobbs Limited

We dispense all NHS prescriptions. We keep a comprehensive stock of prescription medicines and use a fast and efficient wholesaler service to enable us to fill all prescriptions promptly.

 

Please hand your prescription in at the pharmacy counter and the dispensary team will prepare your medication. Our pharmacist is always on hand to answer any questions or concerns you may have about any medication you are taking.

 

You can order your Repeat Prescription  either by calling in or you can order online 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year at:

http://www.hobbspharmacy.co.uk/prescriptions/repeat-prescriptions/

 

At Hobbs Pharmacy, we aim to make living with medication as simple as possible.

To nominate one of our branches to receive your Electronic Prescriptions, simply sign up for a prescription management account with us. If you ever wish to order a repeat prescription with us, you can also do this using the account you created to nominate us. If you have already signed up for an account to manage your repeat prescription, you don’t need to do anything else as you have already nominated us.

http://www.hobbspharmacy.co.uk/electronic-prescription-service/

value.SummaryText:
The Priory Wellbeing Centre, Fenchurch Street is an independent mental wellbeing centre, specialising in the management and treatment of a wide range of mental health conditions and addictions.

The Wellbeing Centre offers expert support on an outpatient basis to help people manage their mental wellbeing. Whatever challenges you are facing, we offer practical, effective help to improve the quality of your life, work and relationships.

What we treat

The Priory Wellbeing Centre offers support and treatment for a wide range of mental health conditions, including treatment for stress, depression, anxiety and addictions. Our highly experienced team includes consultant psychiatrists, psychologists, therapists and other medical professionals.

No-obligation consultation

To understand more about you and your mental wellbeing we offer a no-obligation consultation in person or by phone, if required. This appointment will enable us to tailor a treatment programme to ensure it meets your needs, and provides you with the most effective support for whatever challenge you are facing, book yours today.

Treatment built around your needs

At the Wellbeing Centre you have access to an extensive range of proven treatments and therapies. These include cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT) and mindfulness, through to psychotherapy and dialectical behaviour therapy (DBT). If your GP has suggested a specific treatment, or you have heard of a therapy you think could help you, then contact us to discuss how we can help you.

Click here to download a copy of the latest Priory Healthcare Quality account

Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust is responsible for hospital services at University Hospital Lewisham and Queen Elizabeth Hospital in Woolwich.

The Trust provides a comprehensive range of services to local people in the boroughs of Lewisham, Greenwich and Bexley. It runs a range of NHS community services in Lewisham and some services at Queen Mary's Hospital in Sidcup. In Greenwich, community services are run by Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust.

How can I keep informed and get involved?

To keep informed and get involved you can join us as a member. Membership is free, and we will send you regular information on developments.

value.SummaryText:
The Woodbourne Priory Hospital is an independent hospital, specialising in the management and treatment of mental health problems including addiction.

What we treat:

Acute mental health

Our staff team has the expertise and experience to treat most acute mental health conditions. These include treatment for depression, anxiety, post traumatic stress disorder, obsessive compulsive states and all major acute psychiatric illnesses.

Addiction treatment programme

The service specialises in addiction treatment for substance and behavioural dependency, such as alcohol, drugs, gambling, relationships and shopping.

Addictions treatment programme includes:

  • Free assessment to explore the problem in more detail without obligation to continue into treatment
  • Free weekly aftercare support for 12 months post completion of the 28 day programme
  • Free family support during and post treatment

Eating disorders unit

The specially developed eating disorders treatment programme focuses on the psychological, social, behavioural and physical sides of the illness.

Eating disorder day care services

The eating disorder day care service programme involves assistance in re-establishing an appropriate relationship with food, education as to the nature and consequences of eating disorders and guidance in helping people to identify personally with this information.

Child & adolescent services

Woodbourne Priory Hospital offers outpatient treatment for children and adolescents from 5 to 17 years. This includes adolescents suffering from a wide range of mental health, emotional and behavioural problems such as depression, trauma, schizophrenia, anxiety, self-harm, conduct disorders and autistic spectrum disorders. Outpatient services for children include access to psychology and psychotherapy and is appropriate for those suffering from:

  • Anxiety and depression
  • Obsessive compulsive disorder (OCD)
  • Eating disorders
  • ADHD

value.SummaryText:
Set within a safe and therapeutic environment, the Priory Hospital Dewsbury offers an open rehabilitation service for 32 males. The service has two wards, each comprising of a ten bed unit and six bed self contained apartment. Hartley Ward provides active rehabilitation for males with mental health issues, whilst Jubilee Ward is a slow stream rehabilitation service for males with learning disabilities and complex needs. 


The service complements the psychiatric intensive care and secure services regionally offering a clear recovery focused pathway. Personalised treatment programmes are offered alongside the use of a range of therapies.


Services offered:

• Free initial assessment following referral will be carried out within 48 hours

• Full medical, mental, social and occupational assessments within the first two weeks and the commencement of the recovery pathway

• Multidisciplinary care plan formulation within the first four weeks

• A full care programme approach (CPA) meeting involving both the service users and their carers within the first three months

• Intensive support from the occupational therapy and psychology team as well as medical and nursing teams

• Involving the service user in voluntary mental health groups and offering them access to community activities


Multidisciplinary team:


Our services are committed to a whole person approach. They are supported by an effective multidisciplinary team experienced in rehabilitation, recovery and caring for service users with complex needs. The team includes:

• Consultant psychiatrist

• Staff grade doctor

• Consultant psychologist

• Psychology assistants

• Experienced registered mental health nurses

• Experienced support workers

• Occupational therapists

• Mental Health Act administrator and administration team

• Full hospital support services

• 24hr on-call medical, senior nursing and managerial support mechanisms

Dorothy House Hospice Care is a registered charity which gives care and support to patients, carers and their families across Bath and north east Somerset and parts of Wiltshire and Somerset. 

We provide free of charge, compassionate care and support for people in our community with a life-limiting illness whenever they need it; at home, in our community and at our Winsley Hospice. Our focus is on quality of life, so patients can live well and die well.

Dorothy House VISION: A society where death is a part of life.

Dorothy House MISSION: To ensure that everyone has access to outstanding palliative and end of life care.
